|(until 1934)}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<ref name=\"speakers_1924_1964\">http://ir.uz.ac.zw/jspui/bitstream/10646/3684/1/Willson_Holders_of_Administrative_and_Ministerial_office_1894_1964.pdf</ref>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{United Rhodesia Party/meta/color}}; color:white;\" |1\n|[[United Rhodesia Party|United Party]] {{Small|(after 1934)}}\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{United Rhodesia Party/meta/color}}; color:white;\" |2\n|[[File:No_image.png|80x80px]]\n|{{Sn|Allan Ross|Welsh}}\n|11 March 1935 \u2013 18 March 1952\n|4th, 5th, 6th, 7th\n|[[United Rhodesia Party|United Party]]\n|<ref name=\"speakers_1924_1964\" />\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{United Rhodesia Party/meta/color}}; color:white;\" |3\n|[[File:No_image.png|80x80px]]\n|Sir [[Tom Ian Findlay Wilson]]\n|18 March 1952 \u2013 13 April 1954\n|7th, 8th\n|[[United Rhodesia Party|United Party]]\n|<ref name=\"speakers_1924_1964\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=x3lcBAAAQBAJ|title=The Routledge Guide to British Political Archives: Sources since 1945|first=Chris|last=Cook|date=2 October 2012|publisher=Routledge|via=Google Books}}</ref>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{United Rhodesia Party/meta/color}}; color:white;\" |4\n|[[File:No_image.png|80x80px]]\n|[[William Addison (politician)|William Addison]]\n|13 April 1954 - 30 June 1959\n|8th, 9th\n|[[United Rhodesia Party|United Party]]\n|<ref name=\"speakers_1924_1964\" />\n|-\n! style=\"background: \" |5\n|\n|{{Sn|Walter|Alexander|Walter Alexander (Rhodesian politician)}}\n|30 June 1959 \u2013 28 July 1964\n|9th, 10th\n|?\n|<ref name=\"speakers_1924_1964\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LEeNAAAAMAAJ&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22T.+Williams%22|title=The Parliamentarian|date=10 March 1960|publisher=|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref name=\"google.com\">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3SONAAAAMAAJ&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=stumbles|title=The Parliamentarian: Journal of the Parliaments of the Commonwealth|date=10 March 1964|publisher=|via=Google Books}}</ref>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Rhodesian Front/meta/color}}; color:white;\" |6\n|[[File:No_image.png|80x80px]]\n|{{Sn|Albert Rubidge Washington|Stumbles}}\n|28 July 1964 \u2013 1965\n|10th, 11th\n|[[Rhodesian Front]]\n|<ref name=\"speakers_1924_1964\" /><ref name=\"google.com\"/>\n|}\n\n==[[Rhodesia]] (1965\u20131979)==\n[[House of Assembly of Rhodesia]] was unicameral legislature from 1965 to 1970, and the lower house of the bicameral legislature from 1970 to 1979. \n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! {{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n! Speaker\n! Portrait\n! Party\n! Tenure\n! Notes\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Rhodesian Front/meta/color}}; color:white;\"| 1\n! align=\"center\" scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:normal;\" | Col. [[Albert Rubidge Washington Stumbles]]\n| [[File:No image.png|80px]]\n| [[Rhodesian Front|RF]]\n| 1965 \u2013 31 December 1972\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lnxCAQAAIAAJ&dq=editions:AC1KR95wLwcC|title=Votes and Proceedings of the House of Assembly|first=Southern Rhodesia Parliament House of|last=Assembly|publisher=House of Assembly|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GX1CAQAAIAAJ&dq=editions:AC1KR95wLwcC&focus=searchwithinvolume&q=%22speaker:+the+hon%22|title=Votes and Proceedings of the House of Assembly|first=Southern Rhodesia Parliament House of|last=Assembly|publisher=House of Assembly|via=Google Books}}</ref>\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Rhodesian Front/meta/color}}; color:white;\"| 2\n! align=\"center\" scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:normal;\" | [[George Holland Hartley]]\n| [[File:No image.png|80px]]\n| [[Rhodesian Front|RF]]\n| 27 March 1973 \u2013 1979\n|<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n|}\n\n== Zimbabwe Rhodesia/Southern Rhodesia (1979\u20131980) ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! {{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n! Speaker\n! Portrait\n! Party\n! Tenure\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{United African National Council/meta/color}}; color:white;\"| 1\n! align=\"center\" scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:normal;\" | [[John Moses Chirimbani]]\n| [[File:No image.png|80px]]\n| [[United African National Council|UANC]]\n| 1979\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{United African National Council/meta/color}}; color:white;\"| 2\n! align=\"center\" scope=\"row\" style=\"font-weight:normal;\" | [[John Zwenhamo Ruredzo]]\n| [[File:No image.png|80px]]\n| [[United African National Council|UANC]]\n| 1979\n|}\n==Zimbabwe (1980\u2013present)==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n! {{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n! Image\n!Speaker\n! Tenure\n!Parliament(s)\n!Party\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:{{Zimbabwe African National Union \u2013 Patriotic Front/meta/color}}; color:white;\"| 1\n| rowspan=\"2|[[File:DidymusMutasa1988.jpg|133x133px]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{Sn|Didymus|Mutasa}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{Dts|14 May 1980}} \u2013 1990\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[1st Parliament of Zimbabwe|1st]], [[2nd Parliament of Zimbabwe|2nd]]\n|[[Zimbabwe African National Union|ZANU]] {{Small|(until 1987)}}\n|-\n|[[Zimbabwe African National Union \u2013 Patriotic Front|ZANU\u2013PF]] {{Small|(after 1987)}}\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Zimbabwe African National Union \u2013 Patriotic Front/meta/color}}; color:white;\"| 2\n| [[File:No image.png|80px]]\n|{{Sn|Nolan|Makombe}}\n|{{Dts|2 May 1990}} \u2013 1995\n|[[3rd Parliament of Zimbabwe|3rd]]\n|[[Zimbabwe African National Union \u2013 Patriotic Front|ZANU\u2013PF]]\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Zimbabwe African National Union \u2013 Patriotic Front/meta/color}}; color:white;\"| 3\n| [[File:No image.png|80px]]\n|{{Sn|Cyril|Ndebele}}\n| 14 April 1995 \u2013 2000\n|[[4th Parliament of Zimbabwe|4th]]\n|[[Zimbabwe African National Union \u2013 Patriotic Front|ZANU\u2013PF]]\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Zimbabwe African National Union \u2013 Patriotic Front/meta/color}}; color:white;\"| 4\n| [[File:Emmerson Mnangagwa 2017.png|frameless|131x131px]]\n|{{Sn|Emmerson|Mnangagwa}}\n|{{Dts|1 July 2000}} \u2013 2005\n|[[5th Parliament of Zimbabwe|5th]]\n|[[Zimbabwe African National Union \u2013 Patriotic Front|ZANU\u2013PF]]\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Zimbabwe African National Union \u2013 Patriotic Front/meta/color}}; color:white;\"| 5\n| [[File:No image.png|80px]]\n|{{Sn|John|Nkomo}}\n|{{Dts|1 April 2005}} \u2013 5 March 2008\n|[[6th Parliament of Zimbabwe|6th]]\n|[[Zimbabwe African National Union \u2013 Patriotic Front|ZANU\u2013PF]]\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Movement for Democratic Change-Tsvangirai/meta/color}}; color:white;\"| 6\n| [[File:No image.png|80px]]\n|{{Sn|Lovemore|Moyo}}\n|{{Dts|25 August 2008}} \u2013 27 June 2013\n|[[7th Parliament of Zimbabwe|7th]]\n|[[Movement for Democratic Change \u2013 Tsvangirai|MDC\u2013T]]\n|-\n! style=\"background:{{Zimbabwe African National Union \u2013 Patriotic Front/meta/color}}; color:white;\"| 7\n| [[File:No image.png|80px]]\n|{{Sn|Jacob|Mudenda}}\n|{{Dts|22 August 2013}} \u2013 Incumbent<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chronicle.co.zw/president-meets-parliament-presiding-officers-president-meets-parliament-presiding-officers/|title=President meets Parliament presiding officers|first=The|last=Chronicle|website=The Chronicle}}</ref>\n|[[8th Parliament of Zimbabwe|8th]], [[9th Parliament of Zimbabwe|9th]]\n|[[Zimbabwe African National Union \u2013 Patriotic Front|ZANU\u2013PF]]\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Southern Rhodesian Legislative Assembly]]\n*[[House of Assembly (Zimbabwe)]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Zimbabwe-Speakers of Parliament}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Speakers Of The House Of Assembly Of Zimbabwe}}\n[[Category:Speakers of the House of Assembly (Zimbabwe)|*]]\n[[Category:Lists of legislative speakers|Zimbabwe, Speakers of the House of Assembly of]]\n[[Category:Lists of political office-holders in Zimbabwe|Speakers of the House of Assembly]]\n[[Category:1923 establishments in Southern Rhodesia]]\n[[Category:1980 establishments in Zimbabwe]]\n", "name_user": "Lefcentreright", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSee also:Link",