ld Talbott Tavern]], [[Bardstown, Kentucky]] \n* \"''Get the Ball Rolling''\" - [[Preston School of Industry|Preston Castle]], [[Ione, California]] \n* \"''Souls Adrift''\" - [[National Civil War Naval Museum at Port Columbus|National Civil War Naval Museum]], [[Columbus, Georgia|Port Columbus, Georgia]] \n* \"''Checked Out''\" \u2013 [[Andrew Carnegie Free Library & Music Hall]], [[Carnegie, Pennsylvania]] \n* \"''Spirited Cemetery S\u00e9ance''\" \u2013 [[San Fernando Pioneer Memorial Cemetery|Pioneer Memorial Cemetery]], [[Sylmar, California]] \n|- \n!Overview \n|colspan=\"3\"|\nTwo women capture an EVP of [[Jesse James]] at an historic tavern; evidence of a ball rolling by an unseen force and the voice of a little boy looking for his mother at a reform school for boys; a woman on a tour at a naval museum comes into contact with the spirits of a young sailor from the {{USS|Hunchback}} and Civil War journalist [[Charles Carleton Coffin|Charles Coffin]] on the {{USS|Hartford|1858|6}}; a paranormal team experience unexplainable activity at an old library, from a black shadow mass to a book moving off a shelf; and a green mist manifests during a s\u00e9ance at a cemetery.        \n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:orange;\"|\n|-\n! 5.9 !! Once in a Black Moon !! {{start date|2012|11|30}}    \n|- \n!Locations \n|colspan=\"3\"| \n* \"''Living the American Nightmare''\" \u2013 (private residence), [[Memphis, Tennessee]] \n* \"''A Very Complex Ghost''\" - ''Bonaparte\u2019s Retreat Restaurant & Lounge'', [[Napoleon, Indiana]] \n* \"''Ghostly Guest''\" - [[Hotel Conneaut]], [[Conneaut Lake, Pennsylvania]] \n* \"''Once in a Black Moon''\" - [[Black Moon Manor]], [[Greenfield, Indiana]] \n* \"''The Spirits of Antietam''\" - [[Landon House]], [[Urbana, Maryland]] \n|- \n!Overview \n|colspan=\"3\"|\nA couple buys a house with ties to the occult and discovers the previous owner practiced witchcraft opening a portal to the other side; employees encounter the ghost of a sla