b title|2341199}}\n*[http://www.tv.com/shows/my-ghost-story/ My Ghost Story at TV.com]\n*{{thetvdb|178141}}\n*{{TV Guide|305511}}\n\n{{Ghosts}}\n\n[[Category:A&E (TV channel) original programming]]\n[[Category:Paranormal television]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = ''My Ghost Story''\n| image                = My ghost story-show.jpg\n| caption              =\n| show_name_2          = ''My Ghost Story: Hauntings Revealed'', ''My Ghost Story: Caught on Camera''\n| genre                = [[paranormal TV|Paranormal]]\n| creator              =\n| developer            =\n| writer               =\n| director             =\n| creative_director    =\n| narrated             =\n| editor               = Jon Budd, Lila Cornia, Mike Gallagher, David Harris, Mark Leija, [[David Milhous]], Sef Morris, Juliette Olivarria\n| composer             = Lawrence H. Brown<br />Charles Barth \n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 6\n| num_episodes         = 75\n| list_episodes        =\n| executive_producer   = Mark Phillips<br />Hudie Ayalon   \n| producer             = Eric Anderson, Jason Bourgault, Adam Bain, Gary Basmajian, Joshua Book, Barry Conrad, Ken Davis, Rick Davis, Mark Greczemiel, Nathan Nowak, Brian Phenix, Camille Strayhorn, Renee Tod, Cynthia Calderon Toscano       \n| camera               = [[Single-camera setup|Single-camera]]\n| runtime              = 45 minutes\n| company              = Mark Phillips Philms & Telephision\n| distributor          = [[A&E Network]]  \n| channel              = [[Biography Channel]]<br>[[Lifetime Movie Network]]<br>[[FYI]]<br>[[Travel Channel]]\n| picture_format       =\n| audio_format         =\n| first_run            =\n| first_aired          = {{start date|2010|7|17}}\n| last_aired           = {{end date|2013|09|28}}<ref>{{cite web|title=My Ghost Story|url=http://thefutoncritic.com/showatch/my-ghost-story/}}</ref>\n| status               =\n| preceded_by          =\n| followed_by          =\n| related              = ''[[Celebrity Ghost Stories]]''\n| website              =\n| production_website   = http://www.biography.com/video.do?name=myghoststory \n}}\n\n'''''My Ghost Story''''' is an American [[television series]] on the [[paranormal television|paranormal]], which premiered on July 17, 2010 on the [[Biography Channel]]. The series features [[Ghost story|ghost stories]] told from a person's own supposed experience with the [[supernatural]]. Each episode features claims of encounters at reportedly [[haunted locations]] all over the United States, as well as a few locations in other countries. A spin-off series [https://web.archive.org/web/20120927123114/http://biochannelasia.com/myghoststoryasia/ My Ghost Story Asia] premiered on the [[Biography Channel (Asia)]] on 16 August 2012 featuring stories from Singapore and Malaysia.<ref>[http://biochannelasia.com/myghoststoryasia THE BIOGRAPHY CHANNEL - My Ghost Story Asia] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927123114/http://biochannelasia.com/myghoststoryasia/ |date=2012-09-27 }}</ref> The fifth season started on October 5, 2012 on Fridays at 9/8 Central.<ref>[http://www.facebook.com/pages/My-Ghost-Story-on-AE-Biography/211489736195?ref=ts&fref=ts My Ghost Story on A&E Biography] at Facebook</ref><br />\nThe sixth season which began on August 12, 2013 aired on the Biography Channel, the original broadcast channel, but halfway through the season the broadcast channel was changed to the [[Lifetime Movie Network]] (LMN).\n\n==Synopsis==\nEach episode is narrated by people who tell their own unique [[Ghost story|ghost stories]] and personal experiences of alleged [[paranormal activity]] and supposed encounters with the unexplained in a particular location. These individuals usually start off the show by saying \"My ghost story began when...\" They also show the viewers' visual evidence they claim to have captured on their homemade videos.\n\nEach episode features [[Historical reenactment|reenactments]], video clips, and interviews of people who claim to have experienced encounters with the supernatural. These stories also include some historical facts of the reportedly [[haunted locations]].\n\n==Syndication==\n'''Note:''' The ''My Ghost Story'' series is based on the 2008 and 2009 specials ''My Ghost Story: Hauntings Revealed''. New episodes formerly aired on the [[Biography Channel]] Saturday nights at 10pm [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]. Season two premiered on April 9, 2011. Season three premiered on October 15, 2011. Season four premiered on April 21, 2012. My Ghost Story formerly aired on Lifetime/Lifetime Movie Network. As of 2019, My Ghost Story is currently airing rewreruns on [[FYI]] and on [[Travel Channel]].\n\n'''Warning''': At the beginning of each episode a [[parental advisory]] warning is shown: \"What you are about to see are haunted events encountered by real people. Some may find it disturbing.\"\n\n==Series overview==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=70%\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\"|Season !! Episodes !! Season Premiere !! Season Finale\n|-\n|  style=\"background:teal; height:5px;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''[[#Season 1 (2010)|1]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 8\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{start date|2010|07|17}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{end date|2010|10|29}}\n|-\n|  style=\"background:purple; height:5px;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''[[#Season 2 (2011)|2]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 10\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{start date|2011|04|09}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{end date|2011|06|11}}\n|-\n|  style=\"background:blue; height:5px;\"|\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''[[#Season 3 (2011)|3]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 10\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{start date|2011|10|15}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{end date|2011|12|17}}\n|-\n|  style=\"background:red; height:5px;\