bocker Hotel (Linesville, Pennsylvania)|The Knickerbocker]] (hotel), [[Linesville, Pennsylvania]]\n* \"''Calvin and Haunts''\" - Calvin Center (youth center), [[Youngstown, Ohio]]\n* \"''Playtime in Hell House''\" - [[Exchange Hotel (Gordonsville, Virginia)|The Exchange Hotel]], [[Gordonsville, Virginia]]\n|-\n!Overview\n|colspan=\"3\"| \nInvestigators captured evidence of spirits at an old opera house; a haunted house that was once home to a massacre contains the spirits of poor people who sought to escape the [[dust bowl]]; a couple experienced paranormal activities in an old hotel they purchased including the spirit of the wife's father; spirits launched vicious attacks on two paranormal investigators; and the ghost of a little girl who spent time in a Confederate hospital is captured on camera playing tag.        \n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:red;\"|\n|-\n! 4.10 !! Unholy Hounds !! {{start date|2012|06|16}}     \n|-\n!Locations\n|colspan=\"3\"|\n* \"''Hair-Raising Spirits''\" - The Quequechan Club Mansion, [[Fall River, Massachusetts]]\n* \"''Vox in the Box''\" - (private residence), [[Lynchburg, Virginia]]\n* \"''You Can Check Inn, But You Can Never Leave''\" - The Stone Lion Inn, [[Guthrie, Oklahoma]]\n* \"''Unholy Hounds''\" - Sedamsville Rectory, [[Cincinnati, Ohio]]\n* \"''Cedar House Ghouls''\" - (private residence), [[Cedar Falls, Iowa]]\n|-\n!Overview\n|colspan=\"3\"|        \nA man learns the history of a private gentleman's club, where orbs and EVPs were captured; a couple uses an [[Ouija]] board and brings out an evil spirit that calls himself \"Vox\"; an Oklahoma inn is packed with ghosts who once stayed there; when the ghosts of dogs are heard barking and orbs are captured at a haunted rectory, the current owner discovers its history of dog fighting; and a couple bought a house with spirits that scratched and grabbed the leg of the wife.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:red;\"|\n|-\n! 4.11 !! Let's Scare Them !! {{start date|2012|0