dium]] and her team.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:orange;\"|\n|-\n! 5.4 !! Church of Darkness !! {{start date|2012|10|19}}    \n|- \n!Locations \n|colspan=\"3\"| \n* \"''Ghosts of Conviction''\" - [[Ohio State Reformatory]] (Mansfield Reformatory), [[Mansfield, Ohio]] \n* \"''How the Bell Tolls''\" - (private residence), [[Fort Collins, Colorado]] \n* \"''Spirits of the Departed''\" - [[Confederate Women's Home]], [[Austin, Texas]] \n* \"''Playtime Possession''\" - (1800s house/former hospital), [[Elk Grove, California]] \n* \"''Church of Darkness''\" - Blackbear Church, [[Bristow, Oklahoma]] \n|- \n!Overview \n|colspan=\"3\"|\nDisembodied voices and screams of inmates and the cries of the former warden's wife are heard at a former prison; a man sets up a video camera in his Colorado home and captures a ghost of a girl named Mary Bell who died from [[typhoid]]; the spirits of widows whose Confederate husbands died in the Civil War haunt an elderly home in Texas; a woman gets possessed by the ghost of a little girl while investigating a house in California; and a being known as the \"crawler\" is seen at a destroyed church and its cemetery in rural Oklahoma.  \n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:orange;\"|\n|-\n! 5.5 !! Damnation Plantation !! {{start date|2012|10|26}}    \n|- \n!Locations \n|colspan=\"3\"| \n* \"''He Who Must Not Be Named''\" - (private residence), [[Salt Lake City, Utah]] \n* \"''Leave Those Kids Alone''\" - ''Antiques & Uniques Collectables'', [[St. Augustine, Florida]] \n* \"''Middle Burning Town Hall''\" - Middleboro Town Hall, [[Middleboro, Massachusetts]] \n* \"''Patton Was a Fake''\" - (private residence), [[Gettysburg, Pennsylvania]] \n* \"''Damnation Plantation''\" - (1910 plantation house), [[Lineville, Alabama]] \n|- \n!Overview \n|colspan=\"3\"|\nA teenager is attacked by a tall dark entity in the upstairs apartment where four family members died while living there; the spirits of four children who were hurt by an evil man