urnalist [[Charles Carleton Coffin|Charles Coffin]] on the {{USS|Hartford|1858|6}}; a paranormal team experience unexplainable activity at an old library, from a black shadow mass to a book moving off a shelf; and a green mist manifests during a s\u00e9ance at a cemetery.        \n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:orange;\"|\n|-\n! 5.9 !! Once in a Black Moon !! {{start date|2012|11|30}}    \n|- \n!Locations \n|colspan=\"3\"| \n* \"''Living the American Nightmare''\" \u2013 (private residence), [[Memphis, Tennessee]] \n* \"''A Very Complex Ghost''\" - ''Bonaparte\u2019s Retreat Restaurant & Lounge'', [[Napoleon, Indiana]] \n* \"''Ghostly Guest''\" - [[Hotel Conneaut]], [[Conneaut Lake, Pennsylvania]] \n* \"''Once in a Black Moon''\" - [[Black Moon Manor]], [[Greenfield, Indiana]] \n* \"''The Spirits of Antietam''\" - [[Landon House]], [[Urbana, Maryland]] \n|- \n!Overview \n|colspan=\"3\"|\nA couple buys a house with ties to the occult and discovers the previous owner practiced witchcraft opening a portal to the other side; employees encounter the ghost of a slave in the restaurant basement that was used as a stop on the [[Underground Railroad]]; a guest captures a shadowy figure on a video camera in the ballroom at a lakeside hotel; a [[hobby horse (toy)|hobby horse]] seen moving by itself is caught on camera at an infamous haunted attraction; and a lady with a lantern and an EVP of a little boy are captured at a Civil War-era mansion.\n|-\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:orange;\"|\n|-\n! 5.10 !! Asylum 49 !! {{start date|2012|12|07}}    \n|- \n!Locations \n|colspan=\"3\"| \n* \"''Asylum 49''\" - ''Asylum 49'' (haunted attraction) (formerly Tooele Hospital), [[Tooele, Utah]] \n* \"''Blackford Hospital Horrors''\" - Old [[Blackford County, Indiana|Blackford County]] Hospital, [[Hartford City, Indiana]] \n* \"''Roaming Ghosts of Joliet''\" - (private residence) (formerly Blackburn Funeral Home), [[Joliet, Illinois]] \n* \"''Soldiers of Misfortune''\" \u2013 